.el .ds Aq '
.TH start-tunnel-pinhole-add 1  "add " 
.SH NAME
start\-tunnel\-pinhole\-add \- Add a new IPv6 pinhole
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-tunnel pinhole add\fR [\fB\-\-internal\-port\fR] [\fB\-\-label\fR] [\fB\-\-count\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIGUA\fR> <\fIEXTERNAL_PORT\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Add a new IPv6 pinhole
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-internal\-port\fR \fI<INTERNAL_PORT>\fR
Destination port on the GUA. Omit for a pure pinhole (no NAT, internal == external); set a different value for a port remap (e.g. 80 \-> 443)
.TP
\fB\-\-label\fR \fI<LABEL>\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-count\fR \fI<COUNT>\fR
Number of contiguous ports, counting up from external/internal. Default 1
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIGUA\fR>
The client\*(Aqs global IPv6 (GUA) to expose. Must be an address this tunnel delegates to a client — its subnet needs an IPv6 prefix
.TP
<\fIEXTERNAL_PORT\fR>
External port opened on the GUA
